reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars These work well for library books: one issue with the clear stickies
reviews.reviewText: These are great! Annotating is the best way for me to learn and do my grad work. I cut some to thin strips and also used to fill the page when there was a lot to underline. I also use the smaller size to write key phrases. The markers work well and have a thin and thick option for the tips-I also got some permanent arteza pens that are great, too, because they dry fast. I've also used my frixion erasable pens and sometimes they work, but I prefer the markers/pens that came with the set. **UPDATE: about 7 weeks later, I need to take the stickies out of the library books, and unfortunately, the clear ones leave a sticky residue on some types of paper. I can get most of it off, but some of it smudges. Be aware, and just do a test on the back page or something! (Unless it's your book, of course!!). I would buy again, I would just be more wary of the type of paper if the books is not mine.

reviews.reviewText: For the price, there’s a considerable amount of sticky notes ! All the beautiful colours and sizes are perfect for writing notes in my Bible .The only down side is there aren’t a lot of pens that actually write well on them ….I knew that going into it tho .

These aren’t really clear, they’re more of a cloudy white so that was disappointing. I see in review photos others received what appears to be transparent sticky notes, so not sure what happened here. They will work for what I need them for though, however I chose this pack because I wanted the pen, which I did not receive. It’s not worth the headache to return and I can’t figure out how to contact the seller about the missing piece. Overall my most disappointing Amazon order 👎🏻
